00:20:13.870 --> 00:20:16.420
in the epic poem, Beowulf.

00:20:16.420 --> 00:20:19.220
I love just the alliterative,

00:20:19.220 --> 00:20:21.370
how that rolls off the
tongue, The Width of the World.

00:20:21.370 --> 00:20:25.510
And it really talks about the
world as they knew it back then.

00:20:25.510 --> 00:20:29.310
This is the breadth and spectrum
of the world in this epic poem.

00:20:29.310 --> 00:20:34.030
And in this book, The Width of the
