00:36:33.350 --> 00:36:34.940
Anybody can do that.

00:36:34.940 --> 00:36:38.180
You got to get out and go to
the places, talk to people.

00:36:38.180 --> 00:36:42.080
Being a great writer equates
to being a great listener.

00:36:42.080 --> 00:36:44.590
And listening is a
lost art these days.

00:36:44.590 --> 00:36:47.810
I know I'm up here
speaking to all of you.

00:36:47.810 --> 00:36:49.620
I would much prefer to
be in the back watching

00:36:49.620 --> 00:36:51.630
and listening to all of you.

00:36:51.630 --> 00:36:55.140 position:56%
Because I think being a great
storyteller means that you just have

00:36:55.140 --> 00:36:58.390
to be -- have this insatiable
desire to know things.

00:36:58.390 --> 00:37:00.030
You want to know things
and more things.

00:37:00.030 --> 00:37:01.660
You want to know what
makes people tick.

00:37:01.660 --> 00:37:03.970
So really it's just experience.

00:37:03.970 --> 00:37:06.970
Every writer writes some
stuff based on experience.

00:37:06.970 --> 00:37:08.550
But at the same time,
you have to go out --

00:37:08.550 --> 00:37:11.050
if you want to write about a world,
you have to go out and experience

00:37:11.050 --> 00:37:15.770
that world as best as you can
and talk and sit and listen

00:37:15.770 --> 00:37:19.510
and eavesdrop and overhear the
sorts of people that you're going

00:37:19.510 --> 00:37:21.490
to be writing about,
to make it authentic,

00:37:21.490 --> 00:37:23.800
make it plausible,
and make it realistic.

00:37:23.800 --> 00:37:27.380
Because otherwise, you're just
typing instead of writing.

00:37:27.380 --> 00:37:28.710
Thank you very much.

